I've seen the colour of 'The mother' and the description.
She doesn‚Äôt wish for you SPECIFICALLY to die, just generally.
That is even worse though, in my eyes. She sees it as more 'merciful' for people to die in accidents in her forest...and then literally devours their souls.
What's worse is that her line of thought is reminiscent of many real-world fears.
We always fear death...but in her fear, she has trapped herself in a cage of her own making.
Well that death is a far better conclusion than lost and/or suffering
A leech, feeding off the souls of the fallen in the forest...
Dragging them into her net like a spider to a web.
And yet, in her own web, she has entangled herself!
Like Ungoliant of the Silmarillion, her hunger ever increases. She doesn't even realize she is trapped.
I find her repulsive, and perhaps unforgivable...and yet, in a twisted way, I can't help but pity her, for her fear of death has led to it-would you really consider such a pitiful existence life?
I do, in a way pity the mother. But I fear that she is too far gone...
Then again...there is always hope for change.
